# Polling System API

This is a Node.js-based API for a polling system. It allows users to create questions with options and vote on those options. This API is designed to be open and does not require authentication.

## Table of Contents

- [Project Structure](#project-structure)
- [Setup](#setup)
- [API Endpoints](#api-endpoints)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Optional Features](#optional-features)
- [Contributing](#contributing)
- [License](#license)

---

## Project Structure

The project follows a scalable folder structure:

controllers/v1/
questionController.js
optionsController.js
models/
question.js
option.js
routes/api/v1/
questions.js
options.js
index.js (main application file)
.env (for environment variables)
package.json
README.md

API Endpoints
api/v1/questions/:  To view list of all the questions
api/v1/questions/create: Create a new question.
api/v1/questions/:id/options/create: Add options to a specific question.
api/v1/questions/:id/delete: Delete a question.
api/v1/options/:id/delete: Delete an option.
api/v1/options/:id/add_vote: Increment the vote count for an option.
api/v1/questions/:id: View a question and its options.

Usage
You can interact with the API using a tool like Postman or by making HTTP requests from your application. Refer to the API endpoints section for details on each route.

